18:05.560 --> 18:07.920
<i>BETH:</i>
<i>You hungry, Dad?</i>
<i>You want something now, or...</i>

18:08.120 --> 18:09.880
I want, uh...

18:10.070 --> 18:13.360
I want to figure it out
for myself and-and

18:13.560 --> 18:15.050
you go home.

18:15.250 --> 18:16.970
What?

18:17.170 --> 18:18.670
I just told Ellen
to take a bath.

18:18.870 --> 18:19.890
I'll put it off forever.

18:20.080 --> 18:22.970
I need you to not let me.

18:24.320 --> 18:26.020
Dad, we've barely...

18:26.220 --> 18:29.420
It's all right for you
to not be okay yet. It is.

18:29.620 --> 18:31.240
I'm never going to be okay.

18:32.410 --> 18:34.030
It's the longer I put off

18:34.230 --> 18:36.810
being here by myself, I j...

18:39.680 --> 18:41.330
Help me, Danny.

18:47.160 --> 18:49.260
Try it out for one night.

18:49.460 --> 18:51.310
If you want them
to come back tomorrow,

18:51.510 --> 18:53.140
they will.

18:53.340 --> 18:54.570
Right?

18:54.770 --> 18:55.790
WARREN:
Yeah, that's it.

18:55.990 --> 18:58.180
What I want.

18:59.570 --> 19:00.970
Okay.

19:01.170 --> 19:02.750
You got it.

19:02.950 --> 19:04.540
But we're leaving
our stuff here.

19:04.740 --> 19:06.750
[weak chuckle]

19:20.020 --> 19:21.470
I couldn't let them leave me

19:21.670 --> 19:23.680
if I didn't know they had you.

19:26.250 --> 19:28.070
[sighs]

19:39.220 --> 19:42.270
I need you to take Ellen.
Take her with you in the car.

19:42.470 --> 19:44.320
Okay. Where are you going?

19:44.520 --> 19:46.620
The house on Satsuma
is a shit show.

19:46.820 --> 19:48.320
I've been leaving Arthur
to deal with all of it.

19:48.520 --> 19:51.060
Just distract her. I'll be back.

19:51.260 --> 19:53.200
Don't say anything about us.

19:53.400 --> 19:54.810
Of course.

19:55.010 --> 19:56.760
- I wouldn't.
- [door opens]

20:00.280 --> 20:01.800
[phone ringing]

20:07.770 --> 20:09.650
Hey, Maureen.

20:09.850 --> 20:11.870
<i>MAUREEN [over phone]: I'm so</i>
<i>sorry to bother you today.</i>

20:12.070 --> 20:14.220
Don't worry about it. What's up?

20:14.420 --> 20:17.690
<i>The boss wants to see you</i>
<i>upstairs first thing tomorrow.</i>

20:19.300 --> 20:20.960
Do we know what about?

20:21.160 --> 20:23.350
<i>We don't. Sorry.</i>

20:25.310 --> 20:27.100
Okay. Thanks for the heads-up.

20:27.300 --> 20:29.270
<i>Of course. Take care.</i>

20:30.490 --> 20:32.490
Hey, boss. What's up?

20:34.450 --> 20:36.750
I need to talk to you
about a letter I received.

20:46.500 --> 20:48.600
Okay. What letter, from whom?

20:48.800 --> 20:49.640
Didn't say.

20:49.840 --> 20:52.910
But whoever it is, oh,

20:53.110 --> 20:55.130
- they're accusing you.
- What?

20:55.330 --> 20:56.780
It came directly to me,
and as far as I know,

20:56.980 --> 20:58.040
only to me.

20:58.240 --> 20:59.610
An actual letter, not an email?

20:59.810 --> 21:02.130
Yes. On paper.
It's not vague.

21:02.330 --> 21:04.270
- It's very specific.
- Well, what does--

21:04.470 --> 21:07.780
Actually, forget I asked that.
I know you can't tell me.

21:11.530 --> 21:14.320
- It's with HR now?
- I haven't involved them yet.

21:14.520 --> 21:17.190
You know, you're pretty
important to this office.

21:17.390 --> 21:18.760
Too important, probably.

21:18.960 --> 21:20.280
And when I think about
the kind of shit show

21:20.480 --> 21:21.810
we would immediately be
involved in if...

21:22.010 --> 21:23.550
- Jesus, Marcella...
- Not even to mention

21:23.750 --> 21:26.250
how hard it would be for me
to believe that you would

21:26.450 --> 21:28.510
behave the way that letter is
saying that you did.

21:28.710 --> 21:30.680
Whatever the letter is saying,
I didn't do it.

21:30.880 --> 21:32.300
I'm still looking into it.

21:32.490 --> 21:35.080
I'm keeping the circle
as small as possible.

21:35.280 --> 21:36.690
- Which means what?
- I'm giving it

21:36.890 --> 21:38.740
to Jeannette Ruiz.

21:38.940 --> 21:41.160
[scoffs]

21:43.250 --> 21:45.350
- What would you
like me to say to that?
- She's fair, Dan.

21:45.550 --> 21:47.750
She's fucking scrupulous,
in fact. You disagree?

21:47.940 --> 21:50.700
Good, because you can't.

21:50.900 --> 21:53.620
She's also discreet.
And you're not friends.

21:53.820 --> 21:55.800
- No, we are not friends.
- Which is good.

21:56.000 --> 21:59.190
I'm not friends with her either,
I mean, I need my friends

21:59.390 --> 22:00.190
to have a sense of humor.

22:00.390 --> 22:01.540
But I need my people to

22:01.740 --> 22:03.010
do the right thing,
and she will.

22:04.880 --> 22:06.940
You know, I need for you to
take some time off.

22:07.140 --> 22:09.290
Aw, come on, Marc--
How is that gonna look?

22:09.490 --> 22:10.900
I have a ton of shit
in process right now.

22:11.100 --> 22:12.680
What am I gonna say
is the reason?

22:12.880 --> 22:15.770
Well, in light of recent
tragic family events...

22:15.970 --> 22:18.330
No one's going to ask.

22:24.950 --> 22:27.520
You gonna make Frank
charge my robbery or what?

22:27.720 --> 22:29.180
I haven't read
the transcript yet.

22:29.380 --> 22:30.870
Which means no.

22:32.960 --> 22:34.360
You leaving for the day?

22:34.560 --> 22:36.230
Shit, it's kind of early
to be done, huh?

22:36.430 --> 22:38.400
- None of your business, Earl.
- Right.

22:38.600 --> 22:41.020
Because I never ask questions
that aren't my business.

22:41.220 --> 22:42.890
Basically, it's my whole job,
if you think about it.

22:43.090 --> 22:44.760
My wife's mother died
a few days ago,

22:44.960 --> 22:46.890
so there's a lot going on
at home, a lot to take care of.

22:47.090 --> 22:48.240
- Is that all right?
- Yeah. Listen,

22:48.440 --> 22:49.680
I'm very sorry to hear that.

22:49.880 --> 22:51.420
Thank you.

22:51.620 --> 22:52.770
Still though, you're head
of Major Crimes Bureau.

22:52.970 --> 22:54.200
It's not even 10:00
in the morning.

22:54.400 --> 22:55.940
- Where the hell are you going?
- [sighs]

22:56.140 --> 22:58.250
You know what?
Fuck you for ambushing me.

22:58.450 --> 23:00.210
And fuck you for thinking
you know what my job is.

23:00.410 --> 23:01.990
You think it's a bunch of
ass kissing

23:02.190 --> 23:04.170
and handing out favors when
what it really is

23:04.370 --> 23:06.430
is catching bullshit cases
from bullshit detectives

23:06.630 --> 23:07.910
and trying to make something
out of them,

23:08.110 --> 23:09.820
which I can do
from fucking home.

23:11.780 --> 23:15.610
Hey. My deepest condolences.

23:22.530 --> 23:24.320
<i>DAN:</i>
<i>It's not a bad idea.</i>

23:24.520 --> 23:25.970
<i>MIKE [over phone]: Yeah, well,</i>
<i>it's not a good idea.</i>

23:26.170 --> 23:27.280
<i>Guy's at work</i>
<i>in the middle of the day,</i>

23:27.480 --> 23:28.630
<i>public-facing job.</i>

23:28.830 --> 23:29.720
<i>And suddenly here's you,</i>

23:29.920 --> 23:30.850
<i>even if he knows you got parole.</i>

23:31.050 --> 23:32.460
Well, yeah, that's the point.

23:32.660 --> 23:34.290
Surprise him so we get
an uncalibrated reaction.

23:34.490 --> 23:36.460
<i>Oh, you're gonna surprise him,</i>
<i>showing up saying</i>

23:36.660 --> 23:38.120
<i>he should be a suspect</i>
<i>in the murder</i>

23:38.320 --> 23:39.940
<i>you went to prison for.</i>

23:40.140 --> 23:41.900
<i>You might get an uncalibrated</i>
<i>punch in the mouth.</i>

23:42.100 --> 23:43.900
[chuckles]

23:44.100 --> 23:45.910
I'm not gonna accuse
the man of anything.

23:46.110 --> 23:47.870
I just want him to confirm
that he's the one

23:48.060 --> 23:50.170
that made the unofficial
complaint to Conchita

23:50.370 --> 23:51.520
so I can put it
in the application.

23:51.720 --> 23:53.220
<i>Tomato-tomato, Danny.</i>

23:53.420 --> 23:55.480
<i>But it can't be today,</i>
<i>or tomorrow, anyway.</i>

23:55.680 --> 23:58.180
<i>No, I'm in Pomona on a case.</i>
<i>I need to pay my bills.</i>

23:58.380 --> 24:00.090
<i>So you're gonna have to wait</i>
<i>to get punched</i>

24:00.290 --> 24:01.970
<i>- until I'm done.</i>
- Hold on one second.

24:02.170 --> 24:04.010
- Hey there, how's it going?
- Good, thank you.

24:04.210 --> 24:06.800
Good. Uh, this is awkward,

24:07.000 --> 24:09.670
but I need you to
go down to Central Court today

24:09.870 --> 24:11.110
to file some papers.

24:11.310 --> 24:12.890
Not awkward at all.
Happy to do it.

24:13.090 --> 24:15.940
Okay. Just the idea

24:16.140 --> 24:17.550
that I would ever be asking you

24:17.750 --> 24:19.200
- to go and...
- Jorge.

24:19.400 --> 24:22.240
I appreciate that,
but it's fine.

24:23.890 --> 24:25.600
Great.

24:25.800 --> 24:28.820
- So, could you do it soon?
- Absolutely.

24:29.020 --> 24:30.300
Stop by Suzanne, she's got
everything you need.

24:30.500 --> 24:31.770
Will do.

24:33.250 --> 24:34.220
- Still there?
<i>- MIKE: Yeah.</i>

24:34.420 --> 24:35.520
Looks like I'm gonna go see

24:35.720 --> 24:37.130
Gabriel without you today.

24:37.330 --> 24:39.210
<i>Like you weren't</i>
<i>going to anyway.</i>

24:47.610 --> 24:49.880
[muffled, distorted chatter]

24:50.080 --> 24:52.700
[sighs]

24:57.010 --> 24:59.190
Holy shit.

25:00.320 --> 25:03.720
Benny. Gabriel.

25:03.920 --> 25:06.340
How you guys doing?

25:06.530 --> 25:08.730
Dan Gallagher.

25:08.930 --> 25:12.300
Goddamn, this is crazy.

25:12.500 --> 25:13.950
How long you been out?

25:14.150 --> 25:15.730
Not long.

25:19.380 --> 25:20.830
Can I buy you a cup of coffee?

25:21.030 --> 25:22.790
Judge Curtis in conference now,

25:22.990 --> 25:25.830
so sorry, no time for a break.

25:26.030 --> 25:28.170
All right.
Can we talk, though?

25:37.750 --> 25:39.890
Look, I'm-I'm writing up

25:40.090 --> 25:41.720
- a new trial application.
- Okay.

25:41.920 --> 25:43.020
For who? For you?

25:43.220 --> 25:44.590
Yeah, yeah.

25:44.790 --> 25:46.770
And I found out that you filed
a grievance

25:46.970 --> 25:48.330
against Alex Forrest
before she died,

25:48.530 --> 25:49.770
and obviously,
if I would have known that,

25:49.970 --> 25:51.510
I would have brought it up
at my trial.

25:51.710 --> 25:53.990
Well, if you know, you know
it was unofficial, right?

25:54.190 --> 25:55.820
It wasn't formal.

25:56.020 --> 25:57.560
But it was important enough
to involve your union rep.

25:57.760 --> 26:00.080
That's right, because
that's what they're there for.

26:00.280 --> 26:02.390
They said get it on record,
get insurance,

26:02.590 --> 26:04.610
don't get fired off this woman
who can't take a hint.

26:04.810 --> 26:06.130
And you did exactly
the right thing.

26:06.330 --> 26:08.480
And thank you for being
so forthcoming.

26:08.680 --> 26:11.790
Um, look, I'm sorry.

26:11.990 --> 26:13.750
I didn't have time to
write up an affidavit

26:13.950 --> 26:16.360
before I got here, but now that
we've had a chance to talk,

26:16.560 --> 26:18.060
- maybe I can go draft one
and bring it back.
- Whoa.

26:18.260 --> 26:21.050
Why? I'm not signing shit
for you, dude.

26:25.270 --> 26:27.850
I did 15 years for
a crime I didn't commit.

26:28.050 --> 26:29.720
I'm just asking for your help.

26:29.920 --> 26:32.030
You want to hand my ass over
to a judge to rule on?

26:32.230 --> 26:33.730
[laughs]

26:33.930 --> 26:36.330
Why would I let you do that?

26:42.030 --> 26:45.170
Hey, you don't matter
in this building anymore,

26:45.370 --> 26:46.960
you entitled motherfucker.

26:47.160 --> 26:48.440
You want my help?

26:48.640 --> 26:50.470
Subpoena it.

27:01.660 --> 27:03.570
And you thought
he used to be cranky.

27:04.710 --> 27:07.890
Anyway,
it's good to see you, man.

27:08.090 --> 27:09.070
Is it?

27:09.270 --> 27:11.500
Yeah.

27:11.700 --> 27:13.770
Why wouldn't it be?

27:13.970 --> 27:15.290
I never thought
you killed anybody,

27:15.490 --> 27:18.900
and even if you did,
you still wouldn't be

27:19.100 --> 27:21.160
the worst person I've ever met.

27:24.120 --> 27:26.740
- But you don't?
- No.

27:26.940 --> 27:29.600
Not even with all the rumors.

27:31.340 --> 27:32.700
Can I buy you lunch?

27:32.900 --> 27:34.950
I could eat.

27:36.690 --> 27:40.400
On Fairfax, the Irish bar,
live music type place.

27:40.600 --> 27:44.670
Uh, you and some brunette that
they thought was a witness

27:44.870 --> 27:46.060
in that death penalty case.

27:46.260 --> 27:47.190
You know, the one
with the ranch hands

27:47.390 --> 27:48.150
who killed the guy's ex-wife.

27:48.350 --> 27:49.590
I've never been to a live

27:49.780 --> 27:50.980
Irish music place in my life.

27:51.180 --> 27:52.500
Well, I'm just saying
what was said.

27:52.700 --> 27:54.020
[snorts]

27:54.220 --> 27:56.810
And that you got a fuck pad
in Burbank.

27:57.010 --> 27:58.680
- Wow.
- A condo, or something
like that.

27:58.880 --> 28:00.070
[chuckles]

28:00.270 --> 28:01.680
That you were always
asking people

28:01.880 --> 28:02.900
- to go with you there
after work.
- Really?

28:03.100 --> 28:04.470
- Mm-hmm.
- What people?

28:04.670 --> 28:05.780
I mean, never whoever
was saying anything

28:05.970 --> 28:08.210
would ever say, but...

28:08.410 --> 28:11.300
Holy shit. Well...

28:11.500 --> 28:14.170
- Is there anything else?
- No.

28:14.370 --> 28:16.480
Well, yes.

28:16.680 --> 28:18.660
It's that hot chick in Records.

28:18.860 --> 28:20.790
She drove around in a Porsche,
and for some reason,

28:20.990 --> 28:23.440
people were saying that you
bought it for her,

28:23.640 --> 28:25.870
or leased it,
or whatever it was.

28:27.700 --> 28:29.410
Obviously, it was all bullshit.

28:29.610 --> 28:31.060
Yeah, Benny, I know.

28:31.260 --> 28:33.370
I'm aware I didn't have
a fuck pad in Burbank.

28:33.570 --> 28:35.590
[Benny laughs]

28:35.790 --> 28:37.550
She had a thing
for Gabe, though.

28:37.750 --> 28:40.280
Alex Forrest.

28:41.850 --> 28:44.290
He was always handing me off
all these awesome donuts

28:44.490 --> 28:46.560
that she'd bring for him.

28:46.750 --> 28:50.200
Never said anything, though.
Not till after.

28:53.160 --> 28:55.040
Hmm.

28:55.240 --> 28:56.480
And what about her?

28:56.680 --> 28:58.040
Can I get you another one? Good?

28:58.240 --> 28:59.440
- You ever hear any rumors
about her?
- No.

28:59.640 --> 29:01.180
But I did see her
on the fifth floor once.

29:01.380 --> 29:03.880
By the good vending machines.

29:04.080 --> 29:05.660
With the spicy trail mix.

29:05.860 --> 29:08.450
She was arguing with this guy.

29:08.650 --> 29:10.540
You know who it was?
Or you never knew?

29:10.730 --> 29:12.830
No, I've seen him around.

29:15.440 --> 29:17.240
I think he was in Legal Aid.

29:17.440 --> 29:18.760
Felt like I remember seeing him

29:18.960 --> 29:22.720
in the, uh, in the courtroom
with Ruth.

29:22.920 --> 29:26.510
Low-key guy. Blond hair.

29:26.710 --> 29:28.290
Griffin?

29:28.490 --> 29:31.340
Smith? Biff?

29:31.540 --> 29:33.560
I don't know, khakis.

29:33.760 --> 29:35.170
Man, this place still really
makes the shit

29:35.370 --> 29:36.990
out of some shrimp.

29:45.130 --> 29:46.820
[door closes]

29:53.050 --> 29:55.410
Why'd you come back?

29:55.610 --> 29:57.190
With everything that's going on,

29:57.390 --> 29:58.930
it's been a little hard
to focus at the office,

29:59.130 --> 30:01.370
so I'm gonna prep
from here this week.

30:01.570 --> 30:05.160
Marcella's okay with that?

30:05.350 --> 30:07.330
Yeah.

30:07.530 --> 30:10.380
So I can get Ellen from the bus.

30:10.580 --> 30:13.990
You can stay later at
the office, if that helps.

30:14.190 --> 30:15.720
Okay, thank you.

30:19.860 --> 30:22.780
It mostly helps because...

30:22.980 --> 30:25.600
I don't know how to be
in this house.

30:35.000 --> 30:37.570
[kids chattering]

30:40.620 --> 30:42.540
Hey, snicklefritz.

30:42.740 --> 30:43.980
Mom doesn't wait here.

30:44.180 --> 30:45.410
She waits at the driveway.

30:45.610 --> 30:46.980
I know that.

30:47.180 --> 30:48.810
- I cross by myself.
- Well, I know that,

30:49.010 --> 30:50.640
but I didn't come here because
I thought you needed me.

30:50.830 --> 30:52.420
I came here because
I needed you.

30:52.620 --> 30:54.550
I really wanted to
hold your hand today.

30:54.750 --> 30:56.210
And I might want to
hold your hand tomorrow.

30:56.410 --> 30:58.070
I'm not sure yet.

31:01.680 --> 31:03.030
Are you okay?

31:07.160 --> 31:10.130
Yeah, I'm doing all right now.
How about you?

31:10.330 --> 31:11.610
How you doing?

31:11.810 --> 31:13.520
I am if you are.

31:16.960 --> 31:18.790
<i>ADULT ELLEN:</i>
<i>Gin makes the blood vessels</i>
<i>in your face explode.</i>

31:18.990 --> 31:20.320
<i>DAN:</i>
<i>That's not true, actually.</i>

31:20.520 --> 31:22.010
You know, Grandpa Warren
would be very upset

31:22.210 --> 31:23.150
if he heard you say that.

31:23.350 --> 31:24.710
He always thought of himself as

31:24.910 --> 31:26.540
the global ambassador
for gin's good name.

31:26.740 --> 31:28.460
- What about bourbon?
- Bourbon is prunes.

31:28.660 --> 31:30.020
- What are you talking about?
- Southern Comfort, it's prunes.

31:30.220 --> 31:32.420
Southern Comfort is
hardly bourbon.

31:32.620 --> 31:34.720
And Southern Comfort is
not prunes. That's Dr. Pepper.

31:34.920 --> 31:36.810
And Dr. Pepper isn't prunes
either, so...

31:37.010 --> 31:38.990
So just beer and wine, then?

31:39.190 --> 31:41.380
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah, me too, mostly.

31:41.580 --> 31:43.040
Though there was
a long time there

31:43.240 --> 31:45.600
where I was daydreaming
about Bloody Marys,

31:45.800 --> 31:47.170
which were never really
my thing.

31:47.370 --> 31:48.260
Yeah, it's Mike's thing.

31:48.460 --> 31:50.560
Yeah, that's why.

31:50.760 --> 31:52.610
All those years watching him
knock 'em back,

31:52.810 --> 31:55.530
it symbolized being
out in the world, I guess.

31:55.730 --> 31:57.570
Mm.

31:57.770 --> 32:00.620
But now I'm here,
and all I really want

32:00.820 --> 32:02.570
is a beer.

32:09.010 --> 32:10.760
Oh, man, that's good.

32:10.960 --> 32:12.360
[chuckles]

32:19.890 --> 32:21.160
This is really nice.

32:21.360 --> 32:23.160
And a real head trip.

32:23.360 --> 32:27.040
[exhales sharply]
After...

32:27.240 --> 32:28.990
missing all those years,

32:29.190 --> 32:31.520
to sit here and feel like
I know you,

32:31.720 --> 32:34.300
but to know less about you

32:34.500 --> 32:36.480
than somebody who
barely knows you.

32:36.680 --> 32:39.220
What other people think of
as other people

32:39.420 --> 32:43.090
is really just a projection
of themselves anyway.

32:45.610 --> 32:48.180
What do you want to know?

32:54.580 --> 32:56.810
If it's already built,

32:57.000 --> 32:58.670
why do they call it a building?

33:02.410 --> 33:03.900
Why are they called "apartments"

33:04.100 --> 33:06.070
if they're so close together?

33:12.860 --> 33:14.680
What was it about her?

33:22.690 --> 33:24.950
[Dan sighs]

33:26.220 --> 33:29.050
I don't think it was
actually about her.

33:32.830 --> 33:35.840
Which makes me feel sick
to my stomach to say.

33:36.040 --> 33:39.720
But when I try to remember
what I was feeling

33:39.920 --> 33:41.150
when all that was happening,

33:41.350 --> 33:43.850
mostly I just remember
being afraid.

33:44.050 --> 33:46.460
Of what?

33:46.660 --> 33:49.470
That life had passed me by,
and I didn't even notice.

33:49.670 --> 33:51.730
Hmm.

33:51.930 --> 33:54.990
You're the psychology major...
[clears throat]

33:55.190 --> 33:58.210
and the Jung scholar.

33:58.410 --> 33:59.650
Pretty sure you'd have
a lot more insight

33:59.850 --> 34:00.780
into that than I do.

34:00.980 --> 34:02.650
Well, Mom always said that

34:02.850 --> 34:04.350
your father never
believed in you.

34:04.550 --> 34:06.440
And if that was true,
then you're never gonna think

34:06.640 --> 34:07.880
that you're good enough.

34:08.080 --> 34:10.310
Even if consciously,
on the outside,

34:10.510 --> 34:12.490
you're pushing back, you're
fighting against that idea,

34:12.690 --> 34:15.880
on the inside you're always
just gonna be waiting to fail

34:16.080 --> 34:17.150
because deep down
you really think that

34:17.350 --> 34:18.760
failure is your destiny.

34:18.960 --> 34:22.280
So maybe when you did fail,

34:22.480 --> 34:24.020
when you didn't get to
become a judge,

34:24.220 --> 34:26.070
you just decided to stop
fighting the part of yourself

34:26.270 --> 34:27.770
that secretly thought
that you were worthless,

34:27.960 --> 34:32.240
and instead, just do
something to prove it.

34:38.460 --> 34:40.070
Sorry.

34:42.030 --> 34:43.640
Don't be sorry.

34:45.860 --> 34:47.650
