is how I met him.

35:03.440 --> 35:06.670
And then I got assigned to
another pending case of his

35:06.870 --> 35:08.110
that didn't go.

35:08.310 --> 35:10.590
I have a witness
who places you with him

35:10.790 --> 35:13.680
at Andolini's Restaurant
on the ninth last month,

35:13.880 --> 35:15.120
which was a Friday.

35:15.320 --> 35:18.420
- You remember that night?
- Yeah, actually.

35:18.620 --> 35:20.640
- Can you tell me
what it was like?
- What it was like?

35:20.840 --> 35:23.430
Um, that sounds kind of loaded.

35:23.630 --> 35:26.260
It isn't meant to,
it's just meant to be

35:26.460 --> 35:30.480
open enough to include whatever
you might want to tell me.

35:30.680 --> 35:34.040
I want to tell you everything.

35:37.000 --> 35:38.710
<i>I haven't lived here very long,</i>

35:38.910 --> 35:42.230
so I don't really know
that many people.

35:42.430 --> 35:45.500
I work most of the time, so...

35:45.690 --> 35:47.760
so I was having dinner
at the bar,

35:47.960 --> 35:51.720
and he was there
meeting somebody.

35:51.920 --> 35:54.500
A colleague, I think.

35:54.700 --> 35:58.730
And we just struck up
a conversation.

35:58.930 --> 36:01.900
About work, but more...

36:02.100 --> 36:04.300
more our philosophy of work.

36:04.500 --> 36:07.160
You know, conceptualizing
what we do.

36:08.990 --> 36:10.520
Also, our parents.

36:10.720 --> 36:13.090
Um, our fathers.

36:13.290 --> 36:16.210
His father was a judge.

36:18.300 --> 36:22.960
I don't know, just
good conversation.

36:25.050 --> 36:28.050
I don't really have
many of those.

36:29.180 --> 36:31.930
He made me...

36:32.130 --> 36:35.490
He made me wish that
I had more friends.

36:38.370 --> 36:40.330
Conchita's al--
Sorry, my boss is...

36:40.530 --> 36:43.550
