They took him
in a separate ambulance.

47:14.380 --> 47:16.270
Arthur stayed to try
to reach the owners.

47:16.470 --> 47:18.670
Hon, you can tell me
all about this later.

47:18.870 --> 47:20.710
I don't want you
worrying about it right now.

47:20.910 --> 47:23.360
I thought about my mom,
trying to breathe.

47:24.490 --> 47:27.010
Oh, Bethie, I'm sorry.

47:28.840 --> 47:31.760
I am so, so sorry.

47:33.320 --> 47:35.330
But please don't worry
about this right now.

47:35.530 --> 47:36.950
Just think about Ellen,
think about...

47:37.140 --> 47:39.210
Who's picking her up at the bus?

47:39.410 --> 47:40.950
Sorry. Neurology's here.
They need a few minutes

47:41.150 --> 47:42.780
with Mrs. Gallagher.

47:42.980 --> 47:44.430
Maureen's got her. She's fine.

47:44.630 --> 47:46.220
Wait. They would've
dropped her off an hour ago.

47:46.410 --> 47:48.000
Honey, she knows to go to
the Clarkes' when nobody's home.

47:48.200 --> 47:50.130
Just... She's gonna be fine.

47:50.330 --> 47:53.040
Let the doctor take care
of you now, please?

47:54.170 --> 47:56.270
[sighs]

47:56.470 --> 47:58.230
<i>ADULT ELLEN:</i>
<i>This is all I could find--</i>
<i>"Structural Forms</i>

47:58.430 --> 48:00.710
- of The Feminine Psyche."
- Yeah, I didn't think

48:00.910 --> 48:02.450
there was a lot of Toni Wolff's
own writing out there.

48:02.650 --> 48:05.930
But that, I do remember being
very interesting, though.

48:06.130 --> 48:11.020
The Mother, the Amazon,
the... Hetaira?

48:11.220 --> 48:13.290
Yeah, and the Medium.

48:13.490 --> 48:14.720
Uh, that's not
what Toni Wolff called her.

48:14.920 --> 48:16.640
Uh, Medial Woman?

48:16.840 --> 48:19.810
- Right.
- Immersed in
the psychic atmosphere

48:20.010 --> 48:22.380
and the unconscious.

48:22.580 --> 48:24.470
Yeah. Uh...

48:24.670 --> 48:29.210
"She will often unknowingly draw
the man into chaotic turmoil

48:29.410 --> 48:32.000
"by which she will be
carried away herself.

48:32.200 --> 48:36.050
"She loses herself in ideas
which do not belong to her,

48:36.250 --> 48:38.090
"she experiences the destiny
of another

48:38.290 --> 48:39.830
"as though it were her own.

48:40.030 --> 48:42.050
She becomes the first victim
of her own nature."

48:42.250 --> 48:43.660
<i>DAN:</i>
<i>I should have just</i>

48:43.860 --> 48:46.100
validated the parking myself.

48:46.300 --> 48:48.750
This woman's never coming back.

48:49.660 --> 48:51.750
[Beth sighs]

49:05.720 --> 49:08.160
Can you see a world
where we're gonna be okay?

49:09.590 --> 49:11.080
Or is it too soon,

49:11.280 --> 49:13.510
and you haven't even
thought about it yet?

49:15.470 --> 49:17.510
[phone vibrating]

49:21.950 --> 49:23.880
Hey, Maureen.

49:24.080 --> 49:25.440
<i>MAUREEN:</i>
<i>The Clarkes aren't home.</i>

49:25.640 --> 49:27.270
<i>Is there somewhere else</i>
<i>Ellen would go?</i>

49:27.470 --> 49:29.140
What do you mean?
Did you go to our house?

49:29.340 --> 49:30.670
What is it? What's the matter?

49:30.870 --> 49:32.060
<i>I'm there now, Dan.</i>
<i>I don't see her.</i>

49:32.260 --> 49:33.840
Okay, well,
check the driveway gate.

49:34.040 --> 49:36.110
See if it's unlocked.
She might be in the backyard.

49:36.310 --> 49:38.760
<i>ADULT ELLEN:</i>
<i>"She must express</i>
<i>or act what is in the air,</i>

49:38.960 --> 49:41.460
<i>"what the environment cannot</i>
<i>or will not admit.</i>

49:41.660 --> 49:43.940
"Mostly the dark aspect
of a situation or an idea--

49:44.140 --> 49:46.470
"and she thus activates
what is negative and dangerous.

49:46.670 --> 49:49.420
In this way, she becomes
the carrier of evil."

49:51.420 --> 49:55.120
MACKSEY: So, you're thinking
this might be your topic maybe?

49:56.250 --> 49:58.350
Well, if it is, I'm signing off.

49:58.550 --> 50:01.740
But don't make me chase you
for updates, please?

50:01.940 --> 50:03.560
Mm-hmm.

50:10.220 --> 50:12.060
Okay, this, um...

50:12.260 --> 50:14.580
this isn't my business,

50:14.780 --> 50:16.540
so I'm not gonna ask
any questions.

50:16.740 --> 50:19.280
Just want to help.

50:19.480 --> 50:22.940
So I'm only gonna say...

50:23.140 --> 50:25.720
that you've been seen.

50:25.920 --> 50:28.890
People are talking,
and they know.

50:32.200 --> 50:33.730
I... I really don't know...

50:33.930 --> 50:35.210
You don't have to say anything.

50:35.410 --> 50:38.470
I just...
I-I couldn't not say anything.

50:38.670 --> 50:42.830
"Ruined" is such a weird word

50:43.030 --> 50:46.350
to me to use about people,

50:46.550 --> 50:50.140
about their lives, but...

50:50.340 --> 50:52.740
I've seen it.

50:54.870 --> 50:56.360
Call him again.

50:56.560 --> 50:58.450
He'll call as soon
as he knows something.

50:58.650 --> 50:59.970
I want to call the police.

51:00.170 --> 51:02.710
- Honey, he is the police.
- No, he isn't!

51:06.410 --> 51:08.280
What the...?

51:13.070 --> 51:14.950
Ellen?

51:15.140 --> 51:16.380
[car door closes]

51:16.580 --> 51:18.380
- He knows both of them, okay?
- What?

51:18.580 --> 51:19.820
He knows where to look, and in
the time that it would take us

51:20.020 --> 51:21.820
to explain everything
to somebody new...

51:22.020 --> 51:24.080
No! [crying]

51:28.210 --> 51:30.050
MIKE:
I found her half a block away.

51:30.250 --> 51:32.830
Oh...

51:33.030 --> 51:34.790
Ellen. Oh, my God.
Ellen. Ellen.

51:34.990 --> 51:36.840
It's really important.

51:37.040 --> 51:38.620
The person who took you, did
they tell you who they were?

51:38.820 --> 51:40.580
- It's very important.
- You're right in her face.

51:40.780 --> 51:41.970
- Hey, we need to
do this right now.
- MIKE: Give her a minute.

51:42.170 --> 51:44.060
Ellen, Ellen,
Daddy's not mad at you.

51:44.260 --> 51:45.850
- BETH: Hey, Dan, Dan.
- I just need you to try
and remember.

51:46.050 --> 51:47.240
- Did they tell you anything?
- You need to calm down.

51:47.440 --> 51:48.590
Did they tell you
where they took you?

51:48.790 --> 51:50.200
- Enough!
- Did she tell you who she was?

51:50.400 --> 51:51.630
- Come here, baby.
- What did she tell you? Ellen!

51:51.830 --> 51:52.980
- Dan. Dan!
- Did she tell you her name?!

51:53.180 --> 51:54.120
She's okay.

51:54.310 --> 51:55.630
We got her.

51:57.200 --> 51:59.720
Come on.
Come on.

52:02.460 --> 52:03.860
The FBI is not a decision
that you can unmake

52:04.060 --> 52:06.260
- after the fact.
- I don't care, Mike.

52:06.460 --> 52:07.960
We need to know what
we're gonna tell them first.

52:08.150 --> 52:09.650
- Everything.
- You don't even...

52:09.850 --> 52:11.260
I want to tell them everything.

52:11.460 --> 52:13.440
You don't even know what
everything is yet, Dan.

52:13.640 --> 52:15.660
For your family's sake,
you need a plan.

52:15.860 --> 52:17.700
How are you gonna
platform this, hmm?

52:17.900 --> 52:21.100
The Feds don't answer to you.
They don't consult with you.

52:21.300 --> 52:22.880
They're not gonna keep you
in the fucking loop.

52:23.080 --> 52:25.890
When you ask them to come in,
they come all the way in.

52:26.090 --> 52:30.800
Look... just think overnight.

52:31.000 --> 52:34.020
Beth and Ellen are safe.
Go be with them.

52:34.220 --> 52:37.190
Everything is gonna be
all right. Okay?

52:42.370 --> 52:44.690
[car door opens, closes]

52:44.890 --> 52:47.460
[engine starts]

53:01.390 --> 53:02.920
[cries out]

53:03.120 --> 53:06.660
Get up. I said get up.
What the fuck is wrong with you?

53:34.860 --> 53:36.610
[Dan grunting]

53:36.810 --> 53:39.950
[gasping, choking]

53:50.530 --> 53:52.400
[panting]

53:58.270 --> 54:00.360
[panting, coughing]

54:11.980 --> 54:13.950
I'm going to the Feds.

54:14.150 --> 54:17.300
You think I can't
because you brought her back?

54:17.500 --> 54:19.870
That I won't 'cause
it'll burn me, too?

54:20.070 --> 54:21.570
I do not fucking care anymore.

54:21.770 --> 54:24.530
I'm gonna call in every favor
from anyone who has ever

54:24.730 --> 54:27.490
owed me anything to make sure
that you go away.

54:27.690 --> 54:31.050
[both breathing heavily]

54:32.530 --> 54:35.230
So if you want to die,
you better hurry up.

54:35.430 --> 54:37.840
You don't have much time,

54:38.040 --> 54:40.710
and you'll have to
do it yourself.

54:57.200 --> 54:59.130
<i>[knock on door]</i>

54:59.330 --> 55:01.910
Mikey, I have some
follow-up questions.

55:02.110 --> 55:03.480
Uh-huh.
[laughs]

55:03.680 --> 55:05.000
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

55:05.200 --> 55:09.750
Well, turkey tetrazzini.
Mom supervised.

55:09.940 --> 55:13.400
Meaning she added more sherry,
'cause she assumed I forgot.

55:13.600 --> 55:15.230
Except I didn't forget.

55:15.430 --> 55:18.150
So now it is flammable.
[chuckles]

55:18.340 --> 55:22.240
Also, it's not necessarily
turkey tetrazzini,

55:22.440 --> 55:25.500
it's more like rotisserie
chicken tatrazzini.

55:25.700 --> 55:29.720
And I did forget the mushrooms,
so I just added more cheese.

55:29.920 --> 55:31.460
What's all this?

55:31.660 --> 55:33.990
Ah. The rest of the prints
came back.

55:34.190 --> 55:35.340
Two more hits.

55:35.540 --> 55:37.080
So in addition to
Dr. Paul's buddies

55:37.280 --> 55:39.210
and Gabriel and whoever
Benny's guy is...

55:39.410 --> 55:40.860
- Biff Smithcliff.
- Yeah.

55:41.060 --> 55:44.690
We now have Olena Kuzma
and Elijah Acosta.

55:44.890 --> 55:46.480
So as far as viable
alternative suspects go,

55:46.680 --> 55:49.260
I think we're kind of
cooking with gas here. Hmm?

55:49.460 --> 55:51.180
And we've both had a case
or ten in our day

55:51.380 --> 55:54.700
where more was made
with a lot fuckin' less.

55:54.900 --> 55:59.220
So... I think we deserve
some extra cheese.

56:00.180 --> 56:02.140
Please.

56:10.270 --> 56:12.200
I had a spoon.

56:12.400 --> 56:13.590
- I'll use the wooden one.
- Here, here, here.

56:13.790 --> 56:16.370
Oh, yeah, take that guy.
Do the honors.

