58:31.410 --> 58:33.200
<i>Five, she ramps things up.</i>

58:36.900 --> 58:38.210
[TENSE MUSIC CONCLUDES]

58:38.410 --> 58:40.740
I sometimes wonder,
if I just disappeared,

58:40.940 --> 58:43.830
how long it would take 'em
to notice I was gone.

58:44.030 --> 58:45.610
In five, it's challenging

58:45.810 --> 58:48.440
because not only are we
constructing a story

58:48.640 --> 58:50.710
with so many different
"oh, my God" moments,

58:50.900 --> 58:52.710
<i>but we're also trying</i>
<i>to make sure</i>

58:52.910 --> 58:54.660
that the episode
is not only that.

58:55.220 --> 58:58.100
LIZZY: <i>In that scene,</i>
<i>I see Alex kind of trying on</i>

58:58.300 --> 59:00.930
what she envisions
to be her future,

59:01.130 --> 59:03.760
the life that she deserves
with Dan.

59:03.960 --> 59:04.720
That's nice.

59:04.920 --> 59:06.190
LIZZY:
<i>Alex isn't going in there</i>

59:06.760 --> 59:08.770
<i>with the intent</i>
<i>of harming Beth's mother.</i>

59:08.970 --> 59:10.640
<i>She doesn't know</i>
<i>that she's gonna be there.</i>

59:10.840 --> 59:13.510
The more she lives
in this scene with this woman,

59:13.710 --> 59:17.910
I've felt it was important
to show the resentment building.

59:18.110 --> 59:19.780
ALEXANDRA:
<i>So even though at that moment</i>

59:19.980 --> 59:23.220
in the narrative, you don't know
where Alex has gone,

59:23.420 --> 59:25.570
in her head, you know
she's going somewhere

59:25.770 --> 59:28.600
and that it might
not be good for Sophie.

59:29.080 --> 59:31.660
LIZZY: <i>Family dynamics</i>
<i>are extremely complicated</i>

59:31.860 --> 59:33.360
<i>for Alex,</i>
<i>and so to walk into</i>

59:33.560 --> 59:36.830
what appears to be
this idyllic suburban dream,

59:37.180 --> 59:39.320
I'm not surprised it ignites

59:39.520 --> 59:42.230
some not-so-great
things in her.

59:42.430 --> 59:43.370
SOPHIE:
What are you doing?

59:43.570 --> 59:44.850
What are you doing?

59:45.050 --> 59:46.140
[SCREAMS]

59:50.670 --> 59:52.640
Beth, I think
she was in our house.

59:52.840 --> 59:53.640
What?

59:53.840 --> 59:55.250
I think that she was here.

59:55.450 --> 59:58.730
Beth has to sort of ascend
to this different perspective

59:58.930 --> 01:00:01.080
because she feels betrayed

01:00:01.280 --> 01:00:05.520
<i>but then, pretty quickly,</i>
<i>realizes that Alex is dangerous.</i>

01:00:05.720 --> 01:00:07.390
Right now,
she is very angry

01:00:07.590 --> 01:00:10.300
that things did not turn out
the way that she wanted them to.

01:00:10.690 --> 01:00:12.080
It was very important to me

01:00:12.780 --> 01:00:16.010
<i>that the cheating</i>
<i>never seemed to come</i>

01:00:16.210 --> 01:00:18.310
<i>from anything Beth did.</i>

01:00:18.510 --> 01:00:20.620
<i>I love the voice</i>
<i>that we've given Beth</i>

01:00:20.820 --> 01:00:22.190
<i>in the show.</i>Beth, can you just...

01:00:22.390 --> 01:00:24.410
hold on a sec--No. You want...

01:00:24.610 --> 01:00:25.670
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

01:00:25.870 --> 01:00:27.270
...me to be
by myself right now.

01:00:27.620 --> 01:00:28.410
Trust me.

01:00:28.610 --> 01:00:29.590
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONCLUDES]

01:00:29.790 --> 01:00:30.620
[MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS]

01:00:32.230 --> 01:00:36.250
"Medial woman, she will often
unknowingly draw the man

01:00:36.440 --> 01:00:37.640
into chaotic turmoil,

01:00:37.840 --> 01:00:40.160
by which she will be
carried away herself."

01:00:40.360 --> 01:00:42.900
I think
that there's a huge connection.

01:00:43.550 --> 01:00:45.300
"She becomes the first
victim of her own nature."

01:00:45.500 --> 01:00:47.780
ALYSSA: <i>Whether Ellen is</i>
<i>conscious of it or not, like,</i>

01:00:47.980 --> 01:00:49.130
<i>a huge part</i>
<i>of this character,</i>

01:00:49.330 --> 01:00:51.390
<i>I think, is that she is directly</i>

01:00:51.590 --> 01:00:54.610
and/or indirectly
putting together her story.

01:00:54.810 --> 01:00:57.350
<i>I think she's sort of putting</i>
<i>together who this ghost</i>

01:00:57.550 --> 01:00:59.140
<i>of a person Alex is.</i>

01:00:59.340 --> 01:01:02.230
"...and she thus activates
what is negative and dangerous."

01:01:02.430 --> 01:01:04.530
"In this way, she becomes
the carrier of evil."

01:01:06.960 --> 01:01:08.360
KEVIN: <i>So when you think</i>
<i>about those things</i>

01:01:08.560 --> 01:01:10.630
<i>and you stack them up</i>
<i>all together, I think</i>

01:01:10.830 --> 01:01:11.890
Episode 5 works

01:01:12.090 --> 01:01:14.810
because there are so many
"oh my God" moments--

01:01:15.010 --> 01:01:16.290
[YELLING]
What is wrong with you?

01:01:16.480 --> 01:01:17.980
KEVIN: <i>And then</i>
<i>we end with the largest</i>

01:01:18.180 --> 01:01:21.030
<i>"oh my God" moment</i>
<i>of blood in Alex's apartment.</i>

01:01:21.230 --> 01:01:22.770
I'm going to the Feds.[ALEX SOBBING]

01:01:22.970 --> 01:01:25.290
I do not fucking
care anymore.

01:01:26.590 --> 01:01:27.850
So don't worry.

